data: This attraction was built in 1988, and was the first roller coaster in TusenFryd. The name literally means "the loop". The ride is a custom Vekoma looping coaster with a top speed of 75km/h.

Opened in 2003, Super Splash is a water coaster with a 50° steep second drop, has a top speed of 75km/h. The ride had a total of 3 boats, it was minimized to 2, but for an unknown reason the ride only has one running. Each boat can hold 16 people. The ride is 320m long, and produces a 5m tall splash when the boat hits the water.
Claims to be the "smallest roller coaster in the world" at 2.5 m high, 26 m long, and with a top speed of 6 kph.
A steel sit down coaster that reaches a speed of 40km on a 350 m long track and a height of 17 m.
